sources.title: Alice Of Wonderland In Paris (1966)
sources.description: While in Paris, Alice meets a mouse who takes her on an adventure, during which she meets such famous storybook characters as Madeline and the Frowning Prince.

Young Alice has become a celebrity for her adventures in Wonderland. In her bedroom, she dreams about visiting Paris and sharing adventures with the storybook girl, Madeline.

The film includes adaptations of five short stories:
1. Anatole
2. Madeline and the Bad Hat
3. The Frowning Prince
4. Many Moons
5. Madeline and the Gypsies.

sources.title: Alice of Wonderland in Paris
sources.description: Young Alice, having become a celebrity for her adventures in Wonderland, is in her bedroom dreaming about visiting Paris and sharing adventures with story book girl, Madeline. A talking mouse named Francois rides a bicycle into Alice‚Äôs bedroom and wants to conduct a survey about her favorite cheeses. Alice wants to join Francois in his native Paris, so Francois uses a magical mushroom to shrink Alice to rodent size. Together, they ride through Paris, where Francois narrates a series of short stories such as Madeline and the Bad Hat, Madeline and the Gypsies, Anatole, The frowning Prince and Many Moons. In the end, when Alice finally meets Madeline, it turns out that Madeline dreams of being Alice in wonderland.

metadata.Plot: M. Septime rules the renowned Paris restaurant "Chez Septime" with an iron fist. Grovelling before his rich and powerful customers, M. Septime feels free to treat his employees like children at best or like slaves at worst. M. Septime would be very happy if things just continued the way they are. But Destiny will have it otherwise. Indeed one day, Novales, a South American president, disappears while dining in his restaurant and it looks as if Septime has something to do with it.
